september.title: Frame and Hull First Meeting
september.description: Introduction of SolidWorks Modeling. Determing the key points for the new build - Hull size change, no T-slots, Modular build. Assessing Blastoise's strengths & weaknesses to see what can be improved.

september.title: Computer Vision First Meeting
september.description: Getting to know the team! Went over installation process for Ubuntu, OpenCV, and OIDv4 ToolKit (tools required for object detection). Also discussed the subteam scheduling and objectives.

september.title: Frame and Hull Brainstorm
september.description: Discussed acrylic hull layouts, cable positions, and anchoring cylinders in place. Brainstormed ideas for rotating part/ hold the acrylics cylinders in place.

september.title: Electronics First Meeting
september.description: Introductions and getting to know one another! Determined meeting and workshop schedule.

september.title: First Custom Object Detection Models
september.description: Getting started with YOLOv4 (You Only Look Once algorithm) and Darknet. Training using a pre-labeled dataset to familiarize the team with the process.

september.title: Frame and Hull Meeting
september.description: Discussed potential design problems and locking mechanisms. Began 3D prototyping with SolidWorks.

september.title: EAGLECAD & KICAD Workshop
september.description: Reviewing software for electronic design automation and building PCB boards.

september.title: Autonomy Meeting
september.description: Introducing the basics of state architecture (states, containers, transitions). Also went over some command line commands and the difference between terminals & shells.

september.title: Frame and Hull Meeting
september.description: Brainstormed vertical thruster placements and went over 3D printing process. Beginning of SolidWorks competition to develop ideas for mounting horizontal thruster.

september.title: SMACH Introduction
september.description: SMACH (state machine) is a Python library we utilize to create hierarchial state machine diagrams.

september.title: Controls Meeting
september.description: Familiarizing the team with working with Arduinos.

october.title: Thruster Brainstorm
october.description: Decided on thruster mounts. Vertical & 45 degree mounts.

october.title: Thruster & Legs Design Session
october.description: Determined thruster mount 45 degree design. Began discussions on leg designs.

october.title: Resume & LTSpice Workshop
october.description: An impromptu resume workshop to review the team's resumes and revise for improvements. Additionally, went over LTspice to simulate analog electronic circuits.

october.title: What is Control?
october.description: Overview of states, sensors, and strategies. Reviewed the basics of Arduino.

october.title: Computer Vision Fundamentals & Live Demo
october.description: Went over more fundamentals - localization (where an object is in frame) & classification (what is the object?). A live demo on building their first custom models using YOLOv4 & Google Colab.

october.title: Legs & Harness Design Session
october.description: Agreed on leg design. Brainstorming harness; 3 points of contact and needs to be able to sustain the bot while being loaded on the crane.

october.title: Buck Convertors Tutorial
october.description: Researching buck convertors and principles. Ran a buck convertor tutorial on KICAD.

october.title: Communication Protocols
october.description: GND, DTR, TxD, CTS, CD and more...

october.title: Learning Package Structure, Catkin, and ROS2!
october.description: Instructional package structure review and catkin underlay. Touched on ROS nodes (rospy & roscpp API) as well as publisher & subscribers needed for effective communication.

october.title: Continued Harness Design Session
october.description: Determined harness should be placed between thruster mounts and that u-bolts should be used with carabiners.

november.title: Torpedos, Sonar, & Hydrophone Placement
november.description: Determined that hydrophone placement will be at the bottom of the frame, behind where the torpedo may be. Brainstormed more design ideas.

november.title: Board & Chip Research Session
november.description: Each subteam member chose a different board to research (5 options total). Did a lesson plan for LTSpice (how to import chip & testing), as well as analyze the differences in an AP63300 chip and AP2600 chip.

november.title: Electronics Rack Brainstorming
november.description: Considering design ideas for the electric rack while maintaining that cooling could be an issue for the electronics.

february.title: Jig Design and Laser Cutting
february.description: Worked on jig design for drilling through plates. Also used school's MakerSpace to attempt woodcutting.

february.title: Live Object Detection Demo & Pytorch Introduction
february.description: Reviewing the process for custom object detection models (gathering data, annotating, augmentations, and training). Briefly went over Pytorch usage & use cases.

february.title: Behavior Tree Nodes Introduction
february.description: Reviewed last semester's brainstorming and last year's submarine's electronics rack (Blastoise) pros and cons.

february.title: Continued Electriconics Rack
february.description: Reviewed last semester's brainstorming and last year's submarine's electronics rack (Blastoise) pros and cons.

february.title: Controls Workspace Setup
february.description: Went over installation of Arduino IDE, Visual Studio Code IDE and code formatting.

february.title: Surface-Mount Device & Soldering Workshop
february.description: Practice for surface assembly on the PCB and testing with 13.2 and 16.8 voltage (measuring average voltage, ripple) and loading 3A.

march.title: Tackling the Cooling Issue
march.description: Discussed design ideas for handling cooling within the main hull.

march.title: Soldering Workshop Part I
march.description: Members began to solder hole boards and parts to create a 'traffic light' style board.

march.title: Object Detection Model Showcase
march.description: Shared our custom object detection models made from extracted frames from videos. Discussed what went well and what didn't (speed, accuracy).

march.title: Battery Cable Connectors Discussion
march.description: Created a 3D model for the approach to manage cables and connectors for the submarine's battery.

march.title: GROOT Behavior Tree
march.description: Made a prequalification gate behavior tree for the navigation of the submarine using Growing Robust Trees (GROOT) algorithm.

march.title: Software Requirements Overview
march.description: Designed high-level overview diagram for required software including Ubuntu & ROS2.

march.title: Soldering Workshop Part II
march.description: Team had the opportunity to begin soldering on PCB boards using surface-mount device components. We also tested the boards for the correct voltages & capacities.

april.title: Spring Break Recap
april.description: Researched ORB-SLAM3 algorithm, various ROS2 drivers. Figuring out robot controllers - handhelds, user interface requirements, and the framework (Python + PyQT).

april.title: Getting Started with ROS2
april.description: Introduction to working with ROS2 (nodes, file structure and installation)

april.title: Spring Break Recap
april.description: All plates and six carbon fiber rods have been manufactured.

april.title: Progress Report
april.description: Team finished soldering on the PCB board. Now working with KiCAD again while waiting to wire to the vehicle.

april.title: Working on Interfaces
april.description: Developing Controls interface and Computer Vision interface.

april.title: ROS2 Publisher & Subscriber Nodes
april.description: Completed publisher and subscriber nodes for interfacing with cameras and extracting each frame from video feed.

april.title: Control System!
april.description: Kyogre - control system name for both submarines. Will collect data, run filters & controllers, convert output vector to PVM values(machine code) and write values to actuators & thrusters.

april.title: Progress Update!
april.description: Thruster mounts have been 3D printed and electronic rack has been designed. Next step is assembly and electronic rack manufacturing.

may.title: Semester Recap
may.description: Machine plates, carbon fiber rods, 3D-printed thruster mounts, locking mechanisms, battery cable connectors CAD, racks for side hull CAD, and electronic rack production all done!! Assembly to come.

may.title: Progress Update
may.description: PCB and regulator board done! Soldering complete, but connecting to board holder is next!

may.title: Semester Recap
may.description: Software overview diagram, thruster, controllers, sensor library framework complete! Controls firmware also established. Next is validating sensor libraries & controllers, testing software components, and tuning controllers.

may.title: Progress Report
may.description: Decision to stick with behavior tree, prequalification tree set up! Deciding on search approach & logic for competition tree. Need to finish logic for prequalification and test & develop.

may.title: Semester Recap
may.description: Prequalification object detection model trained. Porting old repository from ROS1 to ROS2. Determined that we will stick with YOLO (version 7 for better speed & less computing need). Need to create object detection node.
